<HEADLINE> Fears Grow for Lost Colo. Child </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RUSTIC, Colo. (AP) -- Four fresh dog teams failed to find any  
sign Tuesday of a 3-year-old boy who disappeared while hiking with 
family and friends in rugged 9,000-foot-high mountains over the 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	Teams planned to expand the search for Jaryd Atadero on  
Wednesday with up to 60 people involved. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are checking under every rock and every log -- and making  
sure we look everywhere the little boy could be,'' said Larimer 
County Sheriff Jim Alderden. 
</P>
<P>
	Jaryd disappeared Saturday afternoon in terrain so rocky the  
search dogs have to wear pads to protect their feet. It was a few 
minutes before anyone noticed the boy was gone. 
</P>
<P>
	``Jaryd is a very strong, mobile kid,'' said his father, Allyn  
Atadero. 
</P>
<P>
	The sheriff said the possibility the boy was abducted is  
``remote.'' 
  	   	
</P>
