</P>
<P>
	MEXICO CITY (AP) -- The Bank of Mexico is ``not concerned'' about  
the current strength of the peso, central bank Governor Guillermo 
Ortiz said today. He told a group of executives from the American 
Chamber of Commerce Mexico that based on Mexico's continued growth 
in exports, ``it is difficult to argue that the peso is 
overvalued.'' The peso has appreciated by about 5 percent since the 
beginning of the year and has been trading at about 9.4 pesos to $1 
for several weeks. 

