<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dead Mom Left in Chair for 5 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ELIZABETH, Ind. (AP) -- A man upset over the prospect of  
arranging his mother's funeral instead left her body in the chair 
where she died for more than five years. 
</P>
<P>
	Relatives in Kentucky asked police to check on Myrtle Petrie,  
saying they had not heard from her in years. Last week, when police 
stopped by her house, they found the elderly woman's bones in the 
chair covered with bedding. 
</P>
<P>
	``The son stated when his father passed away, what they had to  
go through at that time was very upsetting, and he didn't want to 
go through that again,'' said Paul Cesar, the deputy Harrison 
County coroner. The father had died in the early 1970s. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities would not release the son's name but said he  
appeared to be about 50. 
</P>
<P>
	The son was placed in the custody of adult welfare officials,  
and he was admitted for a mental health assessment, said Capt. 
Richard Bauman, a detective with the Harrison County Sheriff's 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
	``He didn't really want to let her go, and didn't know what to  
do,'' Bauman said. ``As time went on ... he was afraid he would get 
in trouble for not reporting the death immediately.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The son told police his mother died in February 1994. She would  
have been 75 when she died. Autopsy results were pending. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
