<HEADLINE> NFL President Joins CBS Web Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- NFL president Neil Austrian has joined a new  
major Web destination that is controlled by CBS Corp. 
</P>
<P>
	Austrian, the new chairman of the venture, iWon.com, will retain  
his positions as NFL president and chief executive officer, the 
league said. 
</P>
<P>
	Austrian helped negotiate the NFL's eight-year, $18 billion  
television contract with ABC, ESPN, Fox and CBS. 
</P>
<P>
	The NFL said Austrian's positions with the league and the CBS  
venture would not pose a conflict of interest. 
</P>
<P>
	``In Mr. Austrian's view, there is no conflict,'' league  
spokesman Joe Browne said. 
</P>
<P>
	One of the founders of the Web site is Bill Daugherty, a friend  
of Austrian's from Harvard Business School, and a former senior 
vice president at the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS is providing $70 million in advertising, promotion and other  
consideration to the Web destination site that aims to entice 
millions of visitors to its other Internet offerings that range 
from business news to sports and entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to links to popular sites, the iWon.com destination  
offers a search and directory service, chat rooms, news and 
entertainment, and other information and services. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal represents CBS's first majority stake in a Web site.  



  	   	
</P>
