<HEADLINE> Phish Fans Go Wild in Iowa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMES, Iowa (AP) -- As far as the chief of police is concerned,  
Phish fans are welcome to stay away from Ames -- forever. 
</P>
<P>
	Chief Dennis Ballantine said Monday the city jail has been  
filled with Phishheads, the devoted followers of the music group, 
since the band's concert at Iowa State University on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``If they never come back, it will be too soon,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	Ballantine said the lawlessness and drug use outside the concert  
was so appalling that he will ask the university to ban Phish from 
campus. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheriff's deputies, police and campus officers say they arrested  
26 fans, most on drug possession charges. 
</P>
