<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wal-Mart To Add, Remodel Stores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BENTONVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- Wal-Mart Stores Inc. will open, remodel  
or relocate as many as 340 stores next year, as well as greatly 
expand the number of distribution centers it operates. 
</P>
<P>
	News of its expansion plans on Tuesday came as the world's  
biggest retailer reported better-than-expected September sales at 
its stores. Wal-Mart continues to woo shoppers with its wide 
selection and affordable prices. 
</P>
<P>
	Wal-Mart's stock rose 93.75 cents to $51.25 on the New York  
Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	The bulk of Wal-Mart's new stores, 160 to 165, will be  
SuperCenters, which combine traditional Wal-Mart discount stores 
with grocery operations. About 100 of them will be expansions of 
existing discount stores. 
</P>
<P>
	About 40 new stores will be the retailer's regular discount  
stores. 
</P>
<P>
	Wal-Mart will expand testing its Neighborhood Markets, adding  
five to 10 units in the fiscal year starting Feb. 1. Wal-Mart's 
Sam's Club division will open 20 to 25 discount warehouse stores, 
with about half being relocations. 
</P>
<P>
	The company also plans to open up to 100 stores in existing  
foreign markets, including Germany and Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	``That doesn't deviate much from what they've been doing. It is  
probably a very manageable growth rate for them,'' said Steve 
Paspal, senior retail analyst at Sovereign Asset Management, a 
subsidiary of John Hancock Funds. 
</P>
<P>
	Kurt Barnard, president of the newsletter Barnard's Retail Trend  
Report, said the expansion will benefit consumers because it will 
intensify competition with rival merchants, which could bring down 
prices at other stores.. 
</P>
<P>
	Wal-Mart also unveiled the largest distribution center expansion  
in its history. It will add four regional general merchandise 
centers, four food distribution centers and two fresh food 
distribution centers. 
</P>
<P>
	As of Sept. 30, Wal-Mart had 1,821 discount stores, 650  
SuperCenters and 453 Sam's Clubs in the United States. It also has 
more than 850 stores overseas. 
</P>
<P>
	Wal-Mart also announced that its sales from stores open at least  
a year rose 7.2 percent in September compared with a year ago, 
while total sales rose 26.4 percent from year-ago levels. 
</P>
<P>
	Wal-Mart benefited from a strong back-to-school season.  
Hurricane Floyd, which hit the East Coast in the middle of the 
month, also helped sales, with shoppers stocking up on everything 
from food to flashlights. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales from stores open at least a year, known as same-store  
sales, are considered the most accurate measure of a retailer's 
business. Other retailers are expected to report their monthly 
sales figures on Thursday. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
