<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Winthrop Soccer Coach Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Winthrop University suspended its men's  
soccer coach for one game for pulling his team off the field with 
26 minutes left in a scoreless game last week. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Rich Posipanko will miss the Eagles game against North  
Carolina on Wednesday, athletics director Tom Hickman said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Big South Conference game at Coastal Carolina on Saturday  
was scoreless when Posipanko pulled his team. Winthrop had received 
one red card and five yellow cards, one to the coach. 
</P>
<P>
	A yellow card can be a warning for an excessive foul and two  
yellow cards become an automatic red card, meaning the player must 
leave the field. 
</P>
<P>
	Posipanko said emotions were running high on the field and he  
wanted to avoid a more serious situation. 
</P>
<P>
	``What I did was wrong and I'm not proud of it,'' Posipanko  
said. However, he said it was the best decision he could make at 
the time. 
</P>
<P>
	Coastal Carolina was awarded a 1-0 forfeit win.  
</P>
<P>
	``We do not condone Coach Posipanko's actions in this matter,''  
Hickman said. ``Regardless of his reasons for doing so, by removing 
his team from the field Coach Posipanko took control of the game 
away from the officials who have responsibility for the arbitrary 
field management and conduct of the contest.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Posipanko also could face additional penalties from the  
conference ranging from a reprimand to an additional game 
suspension. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
