<HEADLINE> Tellabs To Create 2,000 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LISLE, Ill. (AP) -- Tellabs, a Lisle-based telecommunications  
company, announced plans Tuesday for a $75-million expansion in 
Naperville that will include a new office facility and the creation 
of up to 2,300 new jobs. 
</P>
<P>
	The expansion along Illinois' high-tech corridor will be  
supported by infrastructure grants and tax credits from state 
government and the city of Naperville worth up to $30 million over 
20 years, said Brian Reardon, of the state Department of Commerce 
and Community Affairs. 
</P>
<P>
	Tellabs, which designs, manufactures and markets  
telecommunications equipment, has more than doubled its size in the 
last five years. It now has 6,200 employees working in Naperville, 
Lisle and Bolingbrook. 
</P>
<P>
	The new 800,000-square-foot facility proposed for a 55-acre  
Naperville site will probably serve as a new corporate 
headquarters, said Steve Bauer, a Tellabs spokesman. Construction 
is expected to begin in the spring, with an expected completion 
date in late summer 2001. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the jobs created will be at the headquarters, about half  
in research and design, Bauer said. The rest of the jobs will 
probably be in marketing, sales and administration. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
