<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fairfield Football Player Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- A senior co-captain of the Fairfield  
football team was arrested for allegedly assaulting a police 
officer and inciting a riot at a local bar. 
</P>
<P>
	Eric Wise, 21, from Reading, Pa., is due in court Oct. 12 to  
face charges stemming from a melee Sunday outside the Seagrape 
Cafe. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Keith Broderick was one of about a dozen police officers  
responding to the disturbance. Police said Wise was cursing at bar 
employees, and when Broderick tried to subdue him, a scuffle broke 
out. Both men sustained minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	``During officers' attempts to arrest him, Wise was encouraging  
the large crowd that gathered to assist him in his attempts to 
resist,'' Detective Sgt. Gary MacNamara said. 
</P>
<P>
	Wise, a wide receiver, was charged with breach of peace and  
interfering with an officer. 
</P>
<P>
	The Stags are on a 12-game winning streak. Wise had six catches  
for 49 yards in Saturday's 41-14 victory over Central Connecticut. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
