<HEADLINE> Trisha Yearwood To Divorce Husband </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Award-winning country star Trisha  
Yearwood and her husband said Tuesday they are divorcing after five 
years of marriage. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Yearwood and Robert Reynolds, a member of the country group  
The Mavericks, said they have irreconcilable differences. 
</P>
<P>
	They were married in 1994 at the Ryman Auditorium, a concert  
hall that is the former home of the Grand Ole Opry country show. 
They have no children. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Yearwood, the Country Music Association's Female Vocalist of  
the Year for 1997 and 1998, first got attention with her 1991 hit 
``She's in Love With the Boy.'' Her other hits include ``XXX's and 
OOO's (An American Girl)'' and ``Thinkin' About You.'' 
  	   	
</P>
